<subSubSection id="76EC657CFF95FF960DB81E88FA92CA68" box="[199,1304,1267,1293]" pageId="12" pageNumber="373" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="3E4936F7FF95FF960DB81E88FA92CA68" blockId="12.[151,1437,151,1402]" box="[199,1304,1267,1293]" pageId="12" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis id="0C82EAE5FF95FF960DB81E88FEC4CA68" bold="true" box="[199,334,1267,1293]" pageId="12" pageNumber="373">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name “ 
<taxonomicName id="F9F64D74FF95FF960F4A1E88FD1FCA69" authorityName="Wang &amp; He &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2021" box="[565,661,1267,1292]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Bethylus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incurvus">
<emphasis id="0C82EAE5FF95FF960F4A1E88FD1FCA69" box="[565,661,1267,1292]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="373">incurvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to median clypeal carina incurved in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="76EC657CFF95FF960DB81F6DFE2CCA1F" pageId="12" pageNumber="373" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3E4936F7FF95FF960DB81F6DFE2CCA1F" blockId="12.[151,1437,151,1402]" pageId="12" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis id="0C82EAE5FF95FF960DB81F6DFEC8CA55" bold="true" box="[199,322,1302,1328]" pageId="12" pageNumber="373">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from other species of this genus by having LH at least 1.15 × WH, apex of median clypeal lobe distinctly protuberant with apex rounded (
<figureCitation id="A6CD2A72FF95FF960ED51F40FC77CA33" box="[938,1021,1339,1366]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,190,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Bethylus incurvus sp. nov. holotype, ♀. a. Habitus lateral; b. Head, frontal view; c. Mandible; d. Antenna; e. Head, lateral view; f. Mesosoma, dorsal view; g. Mesosoma, lateral view; h. Forewing. Scale bars: 0.15 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775751" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775751/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="373">Fig. 6b</figureCitation>
), and median clypeal carina incurved in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="A6CD2A72FF95FF960C381F24FE13CA1F" box="[327,409,1375,1402]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,190,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-19@11.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 6. Bethylus incurvus sp. nov. holotype, ♀. a. Habitus lateral; b. Head, frontal view; c. Mandible; d. Antenna; e. Head, lateral view; f. Mesosoma, dorsal view; g. Mesosoma, lateral view; h. Forewing. Scale bars: 0.15 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775751" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775751/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="373">Fig. 6e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
